  "conditionals": 13,
  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "Two-component systems in E. coli sense environmental signals via sensor histidine kinases that autophosphorylate and transfer phosphate to response regulators. The EnvZ-OmpR system exemplifies this: EnvZ senses osmolarity, autophosphorylates His243, transfers phosphate to OmpR Asp55, and OmpR~P regulates porin genes (OmpF/OmpC). E. coli has ~30 two-component systems controlling diverse responses. The basic mechanism: signal \u2192 kinase autophosphorylation \u2192 phosphotransfer \u2192 transcriptional response.",
  "id": "ecoli_e._coli_two_component_signaling",
  "keywords": [
    "two-component system",
    "EnvZ",
    "OmpR",
    "histidine kinase",
    "response regulator",
    "phosphotransfer"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
